# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Twilio SMS / messaging-log exports.
#
# Replit's "Saved your changes before starting work" auto-checkpoint will
# happily snapshot anything sitting in attached_assets/, and Twilio's
# Console export drops files like:
#   sms-log-AC<32 hex chars>.csv     <- contains the Account SID + PII
#   messages-AC<32 hex chars>.csv
#   sms-log-2026-04-30.csv
# straight into that directory if you "attach" them in chat. Once a file is
# tracked, pushing to GitHub leaks the SID and customer phone numbers.
#
# Policy: never commit raw Twilio CSV exports. Drop them under
# /tmp/sms-exports/ instead (see docs/sms-exports.md). The patterns below
# are intentionally broad so a slightly-renamed export (e.g. "messages.csv"
# or "twilio-export.csv") is still caught before it can be staged.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
attached_assets/*.csv
attached_assets/sms-log-*
attached_assets/messages-*
attached_assets/twilio-*
attached_assets/*AC*.csv
